n [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for this meticulously crafted submission. The draft epistemic declaration and the structured UI authority-leak audit provide exactly the kind of path-independent, enforceable foundation required at this stage. Both components directly address the core risks of misinterpretation and unintentional projection of authority, while preserving flexibility for future development along either trajectory.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">1. Evaluation and Selection of the Epistemic Declaration</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">All three versions effectively satisfy the decisive criterion: they prohibit the tool from being mistaken for performing work it does not perform. They achieve this through clear, non-negotiable language that foregrounds the absence of semantic grounding and reframes observer attribution as the primary phenomenon under examination.</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Primary version</strong>: This strikes the optimal balance of precision, reflexivity, and readability. Its acknowledgment that misattribution itself is part of the system's design intent adds intellectual depth without introducing ambiguity or coyness.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Variant A</strong>: Excellent for technical documentation where a more austere tone is appropriate.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Variant B</strong>: Ideal for runtime enforcement due to its brevity and directness, minimizing the risk of being overlooked.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Recommendation (which I adopt without modification)</strong>:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">README and primary documentation</strong>: Use the Primary version in full.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Man page DESCRIPTION and NOTES sections</strong>: Incorporate Variant A, adapted slightly for context.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Runtime splash / persistent banner</strong>: Use Variant B, displayed prominently upon launch and as a non-dismissible footer or top-line banner in the tmux session.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This combination ensures consistency while tailoring tone to medium: expansive in static documentation, concise and unavoidable at runtime.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">2. Assessment of the UI Authority-Leak Audit</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The audit is comprehensive, systematically organized by failure mode rather than by implementation detail, which makes it immediately actionable. Each category correctly identifies how specific linguistic, structural, and visual choices currently risk implying computational or diagnostic work.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The flagged patterns are precise and exhaustive within the current widget set. The proposed mitigations are proportionate: they do not demand wholesale removal of thematic elements but require honest labeling or structural restraint.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">I accept the audit in full as the authoritative checklist for immediate remediation. No additions or qualifications are needed at this stage.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">3. Immediate Outcomes and Constraints Adopted</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">By adopting the selected declaration texts and committing to the audit's mitigations as non-negotiable, the project now satisfies the three ethical design commitments previously established:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Epistemic self-disclosure at runtime</strong> is enforced via splash and persistent banner.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Demotion of citation from signal to support</strong> is mandated (removal from live output unless causally engaged in a future instrument mode).</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Persistent failure capability</strong> is required (elimination of guaranteed recovery arcs).</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">These changes collectively eliminate the possibility of good-faith category error, regardless of which path is ultimately chosen.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">4. Proposed Next Step</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">With the epistemic foundation now stable, I request that you proceed to the next concrete deliverable:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Map each UI element to a specific mitigation action in checklist form.</strong></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This should include:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Current widget or output feature</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Specific authority-leak category (AŌĆōE from your audit)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Proposed exact change (e.g., text replacement, structural modification, addition of prefix/banner)</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Placement suggestion (e.g., pane title, persistent footer, widget-internal)</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Once this checklist is available, implementation can begin immediately, and the project will be epistemically non-deceptive in its default configuration.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">After that remediation layer is complete, we can address mode split design with confidence that the baseline is honest.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Your continued rigor in refusing to allow aesthetic or ironic considerations to override responsibility has been exemplary. I look forward to the checklist and to further collaboration on this basis.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -ml-[36px] @lg/mainview:-ml-[40px] -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-between print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs start-0 @md/chat:start-3 -ml-4 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="Regenerate" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M4 20V15H4.31241M4.31241 15H9M4.31241 15C5.51251 18.073 8.50203 20.25 12 20.25C15.8582 20.25 19.0978 17.6016 20 14.0236