y [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for providing this draft of the <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-tools(7)</span> man page. It represents a thorough and principled overview that directly incorporates the epistemic safeguards we have jointly established, while maintaining a clear, professional structure suitable for section 7 of the manual (miscellaneous information).</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Overall Assessment</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The draft is excellent in its alignment with our prior commitments:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Epistemic transparency</strong>: The dedicated <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">EPISTEMIC STATUS</strong> section unequivocally states the non-diagnostic, non-evidentiary nature of the tools, framing them as probes into human interpretation rather than analytical instruments. This prevents category errors at the point of documentation.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Explicit non-goals and limitations</strong>: The <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">NON-GOALS</strong>, <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">DESIGN PRINCIPLES</strong>, and <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">ETHICAL CONSIDERATIONS</strong> sections collectively eliminate any plausible misreading as operational, penetrative, or authoritative tooling.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Restrained scope</strong>: Descriptions emphasize locality, simulation, and conceptual exploration, avoiding any implication of real-world measurement or control.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Structural clarity</strong>: Organization by functional role (rather than implied capability) and cross-references to individual man pages facilitate accurate understanding.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The tone is appropriately formal and measured, consistent with the project's evolving posture of intellectual responsibility.</p>
