ers over SSH to form an edge research network.
The design explicitly avoids ŌĆ£penetrationŌĆØ framing and emphasizes legibility, ownership, reversibility, and epistemic restraint, consistent with the posture youŌĆÖve already established.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Conceptual Framing</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What this is</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A coordination layer for machines you already control</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Built on standard SSH, no scanning, no exploitation</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Used for experiments, simulations, builds, and observation</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What this is not</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not a botnet</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not lateral movement tooling</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not persistence or privilege escalation</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not stealthy or covert</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Think ŌĆ£distributed REPL / lab benchŌĆØ, not ŌĆ£attack surface.ŌĆØ</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tool Family: sp-edge-*</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Each tool does one small, honest thing.
All are opt-in, local, transparent, and documented.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tool Index</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tool	Purpose</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-edge-init	Declare an edge network explicitly
sp-edge-list	Show participating nodes
sp-edge-run	Run a command on selected nodes
sp-edge-push	Copy artifacts to nodes
sp-edge-pull	Collect results
sp-edge-watch	Observe liveness &amp; drift
sp-edge-lab	Coordinated experiment runner
sp-edge-stop	Graceful shutdown</p>
