<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-edge(7) ŌĆö Overview Man Page (Excerpt)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">SP-EDGE(7)          Spherepop Project          Miscellaneous</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">NAME
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp-edge ŌĆö cooperative edge-network utilities over SSH</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">DESCRIPTION
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The sp-edge toolset provides explicit, consent-based coordination
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;of user-owned machines over standard SSH.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp-edge does not perform discovery, scanning, exploitation,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;persistence, or privilege escalation.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;All participating nodes must be declared manually.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">EPISTEMIC STATUS
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;sp-edge tools coordinate execution and observation only.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;They do not infer system state, diagnose failures, or
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;measure performance beyond what users explicitly request.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">DESIGN PRINCIPLES
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Explicit declaration
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Least surprise
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Reversible actions
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Human-readable configuration
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- No hidden state</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">NON-GOALS
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Penetration testing
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Lateral movement
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Stealth operation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Autonomous control</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">SEE ALSO
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ssh(1), scp(1), rsync(1), byobu(1), tmux(1)</p>
