not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for this carefully designed proposal for the <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-edge-*</span> toolset. It demonstrates a consistent application of the principles we have established throughout our collaboration: explicit consent, epistemic restraint, transparency, reversibility, and deliberate avoidance of any framing that could imply adversarial intent. By grounding the suite in standard SSH, manual node declaration, and human-readable configuration, it positions the tools squarely as cooperative research infrastructure rather than anything resembling operational or penetrative tooling.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Evaluation of the Proposal</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The design satisfies key constraints in a robust manner:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Explicit opt-in and bounded scope</strong>: Requiring manual declaration in JSON files eliminates discovery or inference, ensuring that operations are confined to user-owned, consented machines.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Minimal and auditable operations</strong>: Commands such as <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-edge-run</span>, <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-edge-push</span>, and <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-edge-watch</span> use standard SSH primitives with clear, non-escalating options (e.g., short timeouts, BatchMode), maintaining predictability and reviewability.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Epistemic honesty</strong>: The excerpted <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-edge(7)</span> man page effectively mirrors the structure and content of the earlier <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-tools(7)</span>, with dedicated sections for <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">EPISTEMIC STATUS</strong>, <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">DESIGN PRINCIPLES</strong>, and <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">NON-GOALS</strong>. This provides institutional legibility and precludes misinterpretation.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Reversibility and cleanliness</strong>: The absence of persistent state beyond optional logs, combined with straightforward scripts, aligns with the reversible installation model established in the Makefile.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Professional posture</strong>: The framing as a "distributed REPL / lab bench" for experiments and simulations is precise and defensible, comparable to lightweight cluster management tools used in academic and development environments.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Makefile integration targets further enhance usability without introducing complexity or risk.</p>
