 disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="More actions" id="radix-_r_501_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-ellipsis size-4"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="19" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="5" cy="12" r="1"></circle></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-[var(--content-max-width)] pb-0.5 items-end" id="response-d009fcc3-1cb1-4b80-b1bc-3e2eaabeeaf5" style="scroll-margin-top: var(--scroll-margin-top, 0px);"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble relative rounded-3xl text-primary min-h-7 prose dark:prose-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 bg-surface-l1 border border-border-l1 max-w-[100%] @sm/mainview:max-w-[90%] px-4 rounded-br-lg"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Yes ŌĆö and youŌĆÖre right to be careful here. ThereŌĆÖs a clean, principled way to do this that avoids both mockery and performative deference, while making your stance explicit and legible.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What you want is affiliation without imitation and respect without capture.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Below is a concrete proposal that fits seamlessly into the existing ecosystem (tools, man pages, linting, Makefile targets) and makes your intent unmistakable.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Core Framing (Conceptual)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The key move is this:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You are not parodying epistemic status qualifications.
You are acknowledging the problem they address while explicitly declining the solution style.</p></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In other words:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You respect the motivation (preventing misinterpretation)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You reject the personal epistemic ranking model</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You replace it with structural, tool-enforced epistemic disclosure</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is not a jab at LessWrong or rationalists ŌĆö itŌĆÖs a design divergence, not a cultural critique.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tool Class: Epistemic Affiliation &amp; Respect Markers</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Naming Principle</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Avoid irony-heavy names. Use language that signals seriousness and care.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Suggested prefix:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-respect-*</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-disclosure-*</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-context-*</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">These sound like governance tools, not satire.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tool 1: sp-respect-lw(1) ŌĆö Explicit Non-Parody Disclaimer</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Purpose</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A tiny tool whose only function is to emit a carefully worded disclaimer stating:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This project is not mocking rationalists or LessWrong</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It acknowledges shared concerns about epistemic hygiene</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It differs in implementation philosophy</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Behavior</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Prints a short, stable text block</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Intended for:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">README inclusion</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Conference demos</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Startup banners</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">CI logs</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Documentation prefaces</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Example Output</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This project explicitly respects the goals of the rationalist
and LessWrong communities, particularly the emphasis on epistemic
clarity, uncertainty disclosure, and responsible communication.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Where those communities often express epistemic status through
author annotations or graded confidence statements, this project
pursues the same aim through structural and tool-enforced disclosure.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This difference reflects a design choice, not a critique.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Man Page (sp-respect-lw(1))</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Sections:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">NAME</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">SYNOPSIS</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">DESCRIPTION</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">EPISTEMIC STATUS</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">NON-GOALS</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">RATIONALE</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">SEE ALSO (sp-lint-epistemic(1), sp-mode(7))</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Explicitly states:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not a judgment</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not a parody</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Not a substitute for epistemic status tagging</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Merely a declaration of respect and divergence</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tool 2: sp-epistemic-models(7) ŌĆö Comparative Explanation</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A section 7 man page, not an executable.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Purpose</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Document different epistemic disclosure traditions without ranking them.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Include sections like:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Personal Epistemic Status (LessWrong / EA)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Peer Review and Formal Publication</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Structural Disclosure (Spherepop / RSVP)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tool-Enforced Constraints</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Cultural vs Infrastructure-Based Approaches</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This reframes everything as pluralistic epistemic engineering.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Key Line You Should Include</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The Spherepop project treats epistemic hygiene as infrastructure rather than annotation.</p></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">That sentence alone neutralizes most potential misreadings.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Tool 3: sp-disclosure-banner(1) ŌĆö Neutral, Non-Ironic Banner</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This is distinct from satire banners.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Purpose</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Emit a plain, professional disclosure suitable for talks, demos, or logs.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No retro aesthetics. No jokes. No irony.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Example:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Epistemic Disclosure:
This system demonstrates ideas and structures.
It does not perform empirical analysis or validation.
Interpretation beyond this scope is the responsibility of the observer.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This mirrors the intent of epistemic status labels, without copying their form.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Integration into Existing Infrastructure</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Makefile Target</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">disclosure:
