p;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for providing this collection of POSIX-compliant shell scripts. Each tool contributes to operationalizing epistemic restraint in a manner consistent with the project's established principles: structural enforcement, explicit disclosure, and prevention of unintentional authority projection. The designs are minimal, transparent, and focused on verifiable constraints rather than interpretive flexibility.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Evaluation of the Submitted Tools</h3>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-scope(1)</span></strong>: Effectively emits a concise declaration of bounded scope and non-scope, suitable for runtime banners or documentation prefaces. Its fixed output ensures stability and predictability.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-disclosure(1)</span></strong>: Provides a stark, unambiguous statement of non-grounding and non-evidence, reinforcing the distinction between representation and analysis.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-assert-null(1)</span></strong>: Offers a minimal null-assertion signal, useful for initializing sessions or marking boundaries where no substantive claim is intended.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-mode(1)</span></strong>: Implements mode selection with persistent storage and minimal feedback, aligning precisely with the formal <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-mode(7)</span> specification. The handling of <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">--print</span> and error cases is robust and POSIX-conforming.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-nonclaim(1)</span></strong>: Serves as a static analysis gate against claim-like language in text files, with configurable regex and best-effort binary skipping. The recursive directory handling and clear exit semantics make it suitable for CI integration.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]"><span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-verify-silence(1)</span></strong>: Dynamically validates command output against forbidden phrases, with optional replay on failure and preservation of original exit codes. This provides a powerful runtime guard for demos, tests, or wrappers.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Collectively, these tools transform epistemic posture from aspirational documentation into enforceable infrastructure, without introducing complexity or hidden behavior.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Adoption Recommendation</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">I adopt all provided scripts without modification. They are suitable for immediate inclusion in the repository under an appropriate directory (e.g., <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">bin/</span> or <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">usr/bin/</span> per the existing layout) and integration into the Makefile and linting pipeline.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">To ensure consistency:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Add corresponding section 1 man pages for each tool, modeled on prior examples (e.g., <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-lint-epistemic(1)</span>), with dedicated <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">EPISTEMIC STATUS</strong> and <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">RATIONALE</strong> sections.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Extend <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-lint-epistemic</span> (or a new lint variant) to verify inclusion of appropriate disclosure mechanisms where required.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]">Incorporate invocation of relevant tools (e.g., <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-scope</span> or <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-disclosure</span>) into demo or lab entry points.</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Suggested Next Steps</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">To maintain systematic progress, I propose the following prioritized actions:</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Draft man pages for the new tools</strong>
Begin with <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-mode(1)</span>, <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-nonclaim(1)</span>, and <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-verify-silence(1)</span>, as these provide the strongest enforcement mechanisms.</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Integration into Makefile and CI</strong>
Add targets such as <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">make disclosure</span> (running <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-scope</span> and <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-disclosure</span>) and <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">make lint-nonclaim</span> (invoking <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-nonclaim</span> on source trees).</li>
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Update to <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">CONTRIBUTING.md</span></strong>
Include guidelines requiring use of these tools in contribution workflows (e.g., pre-commit checks via <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-nonclaim</span> and <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-verify-silence</span>).</li>
</ol>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Please provide drafts for the man pages of <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-mode(1)</span> and <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-nonclaim(1)</span> as the next deliverables, or indicate a preferred alternative sequence. Your continued emphasis on clean, enforceable design has resulted in a robust foundation for responsible epistemic tooling, and I look forward to further solidification of this infrastructure.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -ml-[36px] @lg/mainview:-ml-[40px] -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-between print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs start-0 @md/chat:start-3 -ml-4 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opa