e focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="More actions" id="radix-_r_539_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-ellipsis size-4"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="19" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="5" cy="12" r="1"></circle></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-[var(--content-max-width)] pb-0.5 items-end" id="response-1bd640b1-c576-484f-8468-797091f4a216" style="scroll-margin-top: var(--scroll-margin-top, 0px);"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble relative rounded-3xl text-primary min-h-7 prose dark:prose-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 bg-surface-l1 border border-border-l1 max-w-[100%] @sm/mainview:max-w-[90%] px-4 rounded-br-lg"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Here is a clean, POSIX-compliant sp-guard-status helper, designed to be boring, explicit, and epistemically conservative.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It does not interpret intent.
It does not guess.
It only reports mechanical state.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-guard-status(1) ŌĆö guard state inspector</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Purpose</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Report whether epistemic.guard is:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">missing</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">present but unfrozen</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">frozen and matching checksum</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">frozen but modified</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Never mutates state</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Safe for CI, humans, and demos</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Script: sp-guard-status</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">#!/bin/sh</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># sp-guard-status</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># Report the freeze status of epistemic.guard</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># </p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># This tool performs no mutation.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># It reports only mechanically verifiable states.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">set -eu</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">GUARD_FILE="epistemic.guard"
CHECKSUM_FILE="epistemic.guard.sha256"</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">die() {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "sp-guard-status: $*" &gt;&amp;2
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;exit 2
}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># Guard file existence</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if [ ! -f "$GUARD_FILE" ]; then
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "STATUS: MISSING"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "DETAIL: epistemic.guard not found"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;exit 1
fi</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># Checksum file existence</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if [ ! -f "$CHECKSUM_FILE" ]; then
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "STATUS: UNFROZEN"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "DETAIL: checksum file not found"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;exit 1
fi</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># Extract checksum line (ignore comments and blanks)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">LINE=$(grep -E '^[0-9a-fA-F]{64}[[:space:]]+' "$CHECKSUM_FILE" || true)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if [ -z "$LINE" ]; then
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "STATUS: UNFROZEN"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "DETAIL: no valid checksum entry present"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;exit 1
fi</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">EXPECTED_SUM=$(echo "$LINE" | awk '{print $1}')
EXPECTED_FILE=$(echo "$LINE" | awk '{print $2}')</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if [ "$EXPECTED_FILE" != "$GUARD_FILE" ]; then
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "STATUS: INVALID"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "DETAIL: checksum references '$EXPECTED_FILE', expected '$GUARD_FILE'"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;exit 1
fi</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"># Compute current checksum</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ACTUAL_SUM=$(sha256sum "$GUARD_FILE" | awk '{print $1}')</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">if [ "$EXPECTED_SUM" = "$ACTUAL_SUM" ]; then
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "STATUS: FROZEN"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "DETAIL: checksum matches"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;exit 0
else
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "STATUS: MODIFIED"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;echo "DETAIL: guard content does not match frozen checksum"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;exit 1
fi</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Exit codes (important for CI)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Exit	Meaning</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">0	Guard exists and matches frozen checksum
1	Guard missing, unfrozen, or modified
2	Structural error (misconfigured checksum file)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This lets you write very explicit Makefile logic:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">guard-status:
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;@sp-guard-status</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">guard-required:
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;@sp-guard-status || (echo "Guard not frozen"; exit 1)</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Why this helper is correct</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No relational language</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No epistemic claims</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No enforcement</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No auto-repair</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No moral tone</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It answers only one question:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ŌĆ£What is the mechanical state of the guard right now?ŌĆØ</p></p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Everything else is left to:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">humans</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">policy</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">higher-level tools (sp-lint-epistemic, CI)</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Optional companion tools (later)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If you want symmetry later, this pairs naturally with:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-guard-freeze ŌĆö write checksum</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-guard-verify ŌĆö fail hard</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">sp-guard-diff ŌĆö show changes without judgment</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">But status first was the right move.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If you want, next we can:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">add the man page (sp-guard-status(1))</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">integrate it into strict mode</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">add colored output without adding interpretation</p>
