t-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 [.last-response_&amp;]:opacity-100 disabled:opacity-0 group-focus-within:disabled:opacity-60 group-hover:disabled:opacity-60 [.last-response_&amp;]:disabled:opacity-60" type="button" aria-label="More actions" id="radix-_r_54t_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-ellipsis size-4"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="19" cy="12" r="1"></circle><circle cx="5" cy="12" r="1"></circle></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-[var(--content-max-width)] pb-0.5 items-end" id="response-6482bbf9-54ee-45b9-8017-caaf5b40fa02" style="scroll-margin-top: var(--scroll-margin-top, 0px);"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble relative rounded-3xl text-primary min-h-7 prose dark:prose-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 bg-surface-l1 border border-border-l1 max-w-[100%] @sm/mainview:max-w-[90%] px-4 rounded-br-lg"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Below is a complete, conservative sp-guard-status(1) man page, written in standard roff style, aligned with the epistemic discipline weŌĆÖve enforced everywhere else. It is deliberately boring, explicit, and mechanical.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No persuasion.
No interpretation.
No relational language.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.TH SP-GUARD-STATUS 1 "December 2025" "Spherepop Project" "User Commands"</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH NAME
sp-guard-status - report mechanical freeze status of epistemic.guard</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sp-guard-status</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B sp-guard-status
utility reports the mechanical status of the file
.I epistemic.guard
with respect to an optional checksum freeze file
.I epistemic.guard.sha256.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The tool performs no mutation, enforcement, or remediation.
It does not modify any files.
It does not interpret intent.
It reports only verifiable file state.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The status is determined solely by:
.IP (bu 4
presence or absence of
.I epistemic.guard
.IP (bu 4
presence or absence of
.I epistemic.guard.sha256
.IP (bu 4
syntactic validity of the checksum entry
.IP (bu 4
bytewise comparison of the guard file against the recorded checksum</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH OUTPUT
The command emits exactly two lines to standard output:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.IP 1. 4
A
.B STATUS
line indicating one of the following values:
.RS 4
.TP
.B MISSING
The guard file does not exist.
.TP
.B UNFROZEN
The guard file exists, but no valid checksum entry is present.
.TP
.B FROZEN
The guard file exists and matches the recorded checksum.
.TP
.B MODIFIED
The guard file exists but does not match the recorded checksum.
.TP
.B INVALID
The checksum file exists but is structurally invalid.
.RE</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.IP 2. 4
A
.B DETAIL
line containing a short, non-interpretive description of the condition.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The output is intended for both human inspection and automated tooling.
No additional text is produced.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status has precise mechanical meaning:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.TP
.B 0
The guard file exists and matches the frozen checksum.
.TP
.B 1
The guard file is missing, unfrozen, or modified.
.TP
.B 2
A structural error was detected (for example, a malformed checksum file).</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The command never exits successfully unless the guard is frozen and unchanged.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH FILES
.TP
.I epistemic.guard
Plain text file containing epistemic disclosure text.
.TP
.I epistemic.guard.sha256
Checksum freeze file containing a single SHA-256 checksum line.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH EPISTEMIC STATUS
This tool makes no epistemic claims.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It does not assert correctness, validity, safety, or meaning.
It does not infer intent or compliance.
It reports only mechanically observable file state.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Any interpretation of the reported status is the responsibility of
external policy, tooling, or human judgment.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH RATIONALE
Freezing disclosure text via checksum provides a simple, auditable
mechanism to prevent silent drift of epistemic guard statements.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Separating status inspection from enforcement ensures that:
.IP (bu 4
the tool remains predictable
.IP (bu 4
the output remains stable
.IP (bu 4
policy decisions remain explicit and external</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This design avoids accidental authority projection while enabling
strict integration in build systems and continuous integration pipelines.</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sp-lint-epistemic (1),
.BR sp-guard-freeze (1),
.BR sp-mode (7),
.BR sp-tools (7)</p>
<hr>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Notes on posture (meta, not part of the man page)</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This page never says ŌĆ£mustŌĆØ except in exit semantics</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It avoids ŌĆ£complianceŌĆØ, ŌĆ£violationŌĆØ, ŌĆ£safetyŌĆØ, ŌĆ£trustŌĆØ, or ŌĆ£alignmentŌĆØ</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">It treats the guard as text plus checksum, nothing more</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This keeps it:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">defensible to skeptics</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">legible to auditors</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">boring to attackers</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">useful to CI</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If you want, next we can:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">add sp-guard-freeze(1) with equally strict semantics</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">wire sp-guard-status into --strict mode</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">add a JSON output variant without expanding meaning</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">finalize epistemic.guard canonical text</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Just say the word.</p></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mr-[36px] @lg/mainview:-mr-12"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Edit" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-end print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs end-4 -mr-2 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-