-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for this meticulously drafted <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-orange-400/10 text-orange-500 dark:bg-orange-300/10 dark:text-orange-300">sp-guard-status(1)</span> man page. It adheres rigorously to the project's standards of mechanical explicitness, epistemic conservatism, and avoidance of interpretive or relational language. The structure is precise, the descriptions are confined to verifiable operations, and the separation of reporting from enforcement ensures neutrality and predictability.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl" node="[object Object]">Evaluation</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Particularly strong elements include:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary" node="[object Object]">
<li class="break-words whitespace-pre-wrap [&amp;&gt;ul]:whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;ol]:whitespace-normal" node="[object Object]"><strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">Mechanical focus</strong>: The <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">DESCRIPTION</strong>, <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">OUTPUT</strong>, and <strong class="font-semibold" node="[object Object]">EXIT STATUS</strong> sections limit themselves to observable file states and syntactic checks, without implying intent, compliance, or broader significance.</li>
